## 🔑 EEG Patterns

| Pattern | Description | Association |
|---------|------------|-------------|
| 3 Hz spike-wave (generalised) | Synchronous bilaterally | Childhood/juvenile absence epilepsy |
| 3.5-5 Hz polyspike-wave | Irregular; photosensitive | Juvenile myoclonic epilepsy (JME) |
| Hypsarrhythmia | Chaotic high-amplitude slow waves + multifocal spikes | West syndrome (infantile spasms) |
| Slow (<2.5 Hz) spike-wave | Generalised | Lennox-Gastaut syndrome |
| Unilateral temporal theta/alpha | Rhythmic; ictal pattern | Temporal lobe epilepsy |
| PLEDS | Periodic lateralised epileptiform discharges | Acute cortical injury (stroke, HSV encephalitis) |
| Burst-suppression | Bursts + flat periods | Severe encephalopathy; deep anaesthesia; status treatment |

