## 🔑 Epilepsy Surgery

| Step | Method | Purpose |
|------|--------|---------|
| Video-EEG telemetry | Inpatient monitoring | Seizure semiology + ictal EEG localisation |
| 3T MRI (epilepsy protocol) | Coronal FLAIR, thin cuts | Structural lesion (HS, FCD, tumour, vascular) |
| FDG-PET | Interictal hypometabolism | Confirms seizure focus (esp. MRI-negative) |
| Ictal SPECT | Hyperperfusion at seizure onset | Localisation adjunct |
| MEG | Magnetic source imaging | Spike localisation, eloquent cortex mapping |
| SEEG | Stereo-depth EEG electrodes | Intracranial recording; mapping eloquent cortex |
| Wada test | Intracarotid sodium amobarbital | Language + memory lateralisation before temporal surgery |
| Neuropsychological testing | Cognitive baseline | Memory, language, IQ assessment |

**Outcomes**: temporal lobectomy ~70% seizure-free (Engel I); lesionectomy varies by lesion type; neuromodulation (VNS, RNS, DBS of anterior thalamic nucleus) for non-resectable cases

